canonical:
  title: 賀親祀大廟牋
  author: 李崇仁
  language: lzh
  text: 大業再興稽古彌文斯爲盛精禋肇擧尊祖敬宗何以加均慶神人增光簡策恭惟功高反正理本無爲致美冠冕之儀告虔粢盛之薦於此於彼求諸陰陽之孔明則著則存僾乎容聲之如在四方咸賀萬福騈臻猥以庸資幸叨重寄受釐宣室雖阻駿奔之班祝聖華封冞殫虎拜之懇
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 賀親祀大廟牋
  author: 李崇仁
  language: lzh
  text: 大業再興。稽古彌文斯爲盛。精禋肇擧。尊祖敬宗何以加。均慶神人。增光簡策。恭惟功高反正。理本無爲。致美冠冕之儀。告虔粢盛之薦。於此於彼。求諸陰陽之孔明。則著則存。僾乎容聲之如在。四方咸賀。萬福騈臻。猥以庸資。幸叨重寄。受釐宣室。雖阻駿奔之班。祝聖華封。冞殫虎拜之懇。
korean:
  title: 친히 대표에 제사 지냄을 하례하는 전
  author: 이숭인
  language: kor
  text: 대업(大業)을 재흥(再興)시키시니 학문과 문장이 이처럼 성(盛)하옵고, 정스러운 제사를 처음 거행하시니 조종(祖宗)을 존경하심이 이에서 더하리이까. 신인(神人)이 경사를 함께하옴에 사책(史冊)에 빛을 더하리로소이다. 공손히 생각하옵건대, 공은 반정(反正)에서 높으셨고 다스림은 무위(無爲)에 근본을 두셨습니다. 관면(冠冕)의 예복을 더욱 아름답게 하시고, 제수(祭需)를 경건하고 성대하게 올리오니, 여기서나 저기서나 음양이 밝은 데서 구하고 나타나고 존재함에 있어 어림풋이 얼굴과 목소리도 계신 듯하오니, 사방이 모두 하례하고 만복(萬福)이 어울려 이르옵나이다. 외람되이 용렬한 자질로 다행히 소중한 직책을 맡사와, 선실(宣室)에 음복주(飮福酒)를 마시는 준분(駿奔)의 반열(班列)에는 비록 참가하지 못하오나, 화봉인(華封人)처럼 성수(聖壽)를 축원하면서 호배(虎拜)의 간절한 정성을 다하옵나이다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0350_010_0480&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: In Congratulation of the Royal Performance of Rites at the Great Ancestral Temple
  author: Lee Sung-in
  language: eng
  text: |-
    The great enterprise blooms anew—
    Ancient learning and refined words flourish abundantly.
    Sacred rites are first begun—
    What greater reverence for ancestors could there be?

    Gods and men rejoice together,
    their blessings inscribed forever in history's pages.
    With humble reverence, I reflect:
    Your merit shines in the restoration of righteousness,
    your rule is grounded in the principle of wu-wei—
    the effortless way.

    Your ceremonial robes grow ever more radiant,
    the altar offerings reach their zenith of sincerity.
    In heaven and on earth alike,
    we seek the clarity of yin and yang;
    wherever manifest and enduring,
    it seems your presence lingers—
    face and voice as if still present.

    From all directions comes celebration,
    ten thousand blessings converge in harmony.
    Though I am but humble and unremarkable,
    I have been graced with this weighty charge.
    I cannot join those who taste the sacred wine in the inner chamber,
    yet like the sage of Huafeng, I offer my deepest wishes for your longevity,
    and with the reverence of the tiger's bow,
    I exhaust the sincerity of my devoted heart.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: 'Wu-wei (無爲): A Daoist concept meaning non-action or non-interference, suggesting natural and effortless governance.'
  - key: ''
    value: 'The sacred wine ceremony in the Xuanshi (宣室): An honor reserved for the highest officials, which the speaker modestly claims not to deserve.'
  - key: ''
    value: 'Huafeng (華封): Reference to the sage who blessed the legendary emperor Yao with longevity.'
  - key: ''
    value: 'Tiger''s bow (虎拜): A deep, reverent form of obeisance.'
